    "collapsible_content_nJrYmE": {
      "type": "collapsible-content",
      "blocks": {
        "collapsible_row_content_6w9ntk": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What surfaces can I use it on?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>It is designed for common hard-cleaning areas like bathroom tile, tubs, floors, grout, sinks, faucets, kitchen counters, stovetops, and backsplashes. For delicate finishes, test a small hidden area first and use the gentlest suitable attachment.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_njkpDd": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Is the handle telescopic?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. The handle extends so you can reach lower floors, taller shower walls, and awkward corners more comfortably than with a short handheld scrubber.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_CVU4Bm": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Can I use it as a handheld brush too?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. You can use the main unit by itself for tighter jobs like sinks, faucet bases, corners, and stovetop cleanup, then attach the pole when you need more reach.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_ETX7yr": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "What do the 9 brush heads help with?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>The different heads make it easier to handle flat surfaces, grout lines, curved areas, corners, and more targeted scrubbing tasks. That means you are not forcing one brush shape to do every job.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_HTVjPX": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Is it suitable for bathroom floors and shower walls?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. That is one of the main use cases. The longer handle is helpful for bathroom floors, tubs, tile walls, and other large wet areas that usually require kneeling or stretching.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_Ahw39W": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Can I use it in the kitchen?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>Yes. It is useful for sinks, counters, backsplashes, and greasy buildup on sealed kitchen surfaces. Avoid using it on hot surfaces, and always pair it with an appropriate cleaner for the mess you are tackling.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "collapsible_row_content_z4rFdy": {
          "type": "collapsible-row-content",
          "settings": {
            "open": false,
            "heading": "Do I need to press hard while cleaning?",
            "icon": "",
            "filled_icon": false,
            "row_content": "<p>No. Let the electric scrubbing action do most of the work. Light, steady guidance is usually more effective and helps reduce unnecessary wear on both the attachment and the surface.</p>",
            "page": ""
          },
          "blocks": {}
        }
      },
